title: Codru-Moma Mountains
data: The Codru-Moma Mountains (Munții Codru-Moma) are a part of the Apuseni Mountains. They are specifically located in the Arad and Bihor counties,[1] within the Western Romanian Carpathians of Crișana, Romania.[2] 46°32′11″N 22°10′33″E﻿ / ﻿46.5364°N 22.1758°E﻿ / 46.5364; 22.1758 This Romanian location article is a stub.
